The number of recruits from Ukraine preparing to be sent to Donbass has been named
The official representative of the People's Militia of the self-proclaimed Luhansk People's Republic (LPR), Andriy Marochko, said that in the winter of 2018-2019, Ukraine will send at least 3 thousand recruits to Donbass.
According to him, in this way Kiev plans to "somehow complete the units."
"The reluctance of Ukrainian citizens to serve in the ranks of the Armed Forces of Ukraine, mass dismissals led to low staffing of units," Marochko said, as quoted by RIA Novosti.
He also did not rule out that the real numbers of Ukrainians drafted into the army could be increased if necessary.
In 2014-2017, Kiev launched the so-called anti-terrorist operation (ATO), which was later replaced by the Joint Forces Operation (JFO).
It was assumed that this measure would lead to an increase in the role of the Ukrainian security forces in resolving the situation.
At the end of August 2018, the situation in the Donbass escalated due to the murder of the head of the DPR Alexander Zakharchenko.
The DPR authorities qualified the incident as a terrorist attack.
During the investigation of the criminal case, several people involved in the explosion were detained.
According to preliminary data, they confirmed that the sabotage was organized by the Ukrainian special services.
US authorities forced Musk to leave the post of chairman of the board of Tesla
American businessman Elon Musk will leave the post of chairman of the board of directors of the company Tesla founded by him at the request of the US authorities.
To settle claims of the Federal Securities and Exchange Commission, the entrepreneur will also pay $ 20 million.
According to CNBC, the pre-trial agreement with the department allows Musk to remain in a senior position at Tesla.
At the same time, he is obliged to pay $ 20 million and leave the post of chairman of the board of directors within 45 days from the date of the agreement and for at least three years.
Two independent directors will be appointed in his place.
It is specified that the agreement has yet to be approved by the court.
On September 28, it became known that the US Securities and Exchange Commission accused Musk of misleading shareholders with a statement that there were sufficient funds to buy back shares of this company and sued the entrepreneur in court.
We are talking about the publication of the businessman on Twitter, where he announced his desire to buy Tesla shares at $ 420 apiece, but did not do it.
After the tweet, the company's shares rose by almost 11%.
The head of the British Foreign Office compared the EU with the Soviet Union and prison
British Foreign Secretary Jeremy Hunt compared the European Union to the Soviet Union and accused Brussels of capturing the member states of the community.
The diplomat made such a statement at the congress of the ruling Conservative Party in Birmingham, which opened on Sunday, September 30.
As noted by the Daily Mail, in this way Hunt commented on the difficulties in the negotiation process on Brexit.
What happened to the belief in the European dream and its ideals?
The EU was created to protect freedom, and the Soviet Union did not allow anyone to leave it.
The lesson of history is obvious: if you turn the EU from a community into a prison, the desire to leave it will not decrease, but will only grow, and we will not be the only prisoner who wants to escape from captivity," the minister said.
He also added that attempts to punish Britain for the decision to leave the European Union will only exacerbate the crisis, Gazeta.ru notes.
In mid-September, British Prime Minister Theresa May said that Brexit negotiations had reached an impasse.
So she commented on the results of the informal summit of the European Union in Salzburg.
The decision on Brexit was made in 2016 following a referendum.
It is expected that the withdrawal of the United Kingdom should take place before April 2019, but negotiations with Brussels on this issue are complicated by many factors.
In particular, there is still no clear agreement on how the parties will interact after London leaves the community.
In addition, the question of the Irish border remains open.
The President of South Korea who received mushrooms from the DPRK was presented with two dogs
South Korean President Moon Jae-in received two puppies as a gift from North Korean leader Kim Jong-un after a visit to Pyongyang.
It is reported by Reuters with reference to the representative of the administration of the South Korean president.
"During the summit, a pair of Pongsan dogs were offered as a gift.
On Thursday, they were received," the department said.
The dogs are about a year old, "as an aid for their adaptation," the North Korean side handed over several kilograms of food.
The gift was made in honor of the inter-Korean summit, which was held from September 18 to 20 in Pyongyang.
The Hunting Breed Pongsan is from North Korean wolves and got its name from one of the districts of the DPRK.
As the agency notes, Moon loves animals, he already has two such dogs, which were given to him by the former leader of North Korea, Kim Jong-il.
Dogs aren't the only gift.
Kim Jong-un also handed over to his colleague two tons of delicatessen matsutake mushrooms.
He ordered to distribute these mushrooms to members of families separated during the Korean War, who have not yet reunited with their loved ones from the DPRK.
The head of the Altai village council stopped the hunger strike in defense of the interests of residents
The mp said on his Facebook page that he had stopped starving for several reasons.
The head of the village council said that the situation has reached an impasse, the district administration does not respond to his demands, and he needs to do his job.
In addition, the prosecutor's office began to check the situation, and the heat supply organization STPK promised to begin work on preparing the system for the passage of the winter heating period of the village of Sibirsky next week.
Also, residents of the village council made and took away to the governor of the Altai Territory a mass collective appeal "concerning the current catastrophic situation."
