Named new buildings in Moscow with the cheapest apartments
In the first half of 2018, about three thousand housing units with an area of 30 square meters and a cost of up to four million rubles were bought in new buildings in Moscow.
More than half of such transactions accounted for two residential complexes, according to the materials of the Portal Urbanus (available to Lenta.ru).
The leaders in terms of housing sales in the budget of up to four million rubles were the Nekrasovka residential complex, located behind the Moscow Ring Road, in the Kotelniki district (Southeast Asia), and the Barbaris apartment complex in the Bibirevo district (SVAO).
Notable in the structure of transactions with budget housing were also two residential complexes in New Moscow - "Southern Bunino" and "Maple Alleys".
Urbanus analysts note that the share of transactions with apartments up to four million rubles in these new buildings reaches 60 percent of all sales and provides half of the total revenue.
"It is necessary to recognize the impact of apartments with a budget of less than four million rubles on the commercial success of the Tsentralny microdistrict in Novye Vatutinki and the Filatov Lug residential complex," the study says about two more residential complexes in New Moscow.
At their expense, about 35 percent of the volume of financial revenues is formed.
Earlier, the rating of districts of Moscow with the cheapest apartments in new buildings was presented in the real estate agency "Bon Ton".
According to the company, the lowest prices for primary housing (149.9 thousand rubles per meter) in September 2018 were recorded in Southeast Asia.
In second and third place were VAO and SVAO with indicators of 184.1 and 192.8 thousand rubles, respectively.
