Grand Prix in Sochi: full house, Russian car and the return of Kvyat
Over the next ten years, Russia may have its own racing car.
Russian Deputy Prime Minister Dmitry Kozak said this, summing up the results of a meeting with Russian automakers on the eve of the start of the Russian Grand Prix in Sochi.
Also, the Deputy Prime Minister shared his opinion on the return of Daniil Kvyat to Toro Rosso and assessed the attendance of the Russian stage of Formula 1.
The result of our meeting with automakers should be in the foreseeable future just the creation of the Russian Formula 1 car, which has no analogues in the world, - said Dmitry Kozak.
We need to stimulate our automakers in this direction.
It was about plans until 2024, but I do not think that in such a time frame it is possible.
I think it's a more realistic timeline over the next ten years."
From 2012 to 2014, the Marusya team competed in Formula 1 under a Russian license.
According to the Deputy Prime Minister, there are already investors who are ready to invest in the creation of a domestic team in the World Championship in auto racing in the Formula 1 class.
I know that in Russia there are fans of motor sports, wealthy businessmen who are ready to invest, ready to invest in the creation of the Russian Formula 1 team," he said.
"We are ready to support them morally.
Let's hope that we will have such a team.
I suspect that thoughts about the creation of a team appeared, among other things, because such an infrastructure appeared in Sochi."
Tomorrow "Sochi Autodrom" is waiting for a full house.
According to Dmitry Kozak, the organizers managed to sell all 50 thousand tickets.
Look, even at the qualification, the stands were practically filled, - said the Deputy Prime Minister.
I can say that revenue this year has grown by 72% compared to last year.
