Let's hope that next season there will be more of our main pilots than this year, - said Dmitry Kozak.
In Indonesia, after the earthquake, more than 100 prisoners escaped from prison
More than 100 inmates have escaped from a prison in Indonesia's Central Sulawesi province.
The escape became possible after two powerful earthquakes on the island of magnitude 7.2 and 7.4.
According to the newspaper The Jakarta Post, the incident occurred on September 28, when prisoners in the prison of the city of Palu demanded their release in connection with tremors.
More than 340 prisoners rioted and set fire to the institution.
The police who arrived at the scene of the emergency partially took control of the situation, but more than 100 people escaped from the prison.
The building itself has been severely damaged, and the guards are struggling to hold the prisoners.
The number of victims of the earthquake and tsunami that occurred on the island of Sulawesi has risen to 832 people.
As a result, it is still not possible to establish transport, electricity and communication with some parts of the island.
"Golden Pearl" for "ultimate realism"
The International Film Festival in San Sebastian for the third time in history recognized the Spanish film of the year as the best film of the year.
The main award - "Golden Shell" - was awarded to the drama "Between Two Seas" directed by Isaki Lacuesta.
This film with almost documentary realism tells the difficult story of the life of two brothers in the Spanish coastal province of Cadiz - Lacuesta presented the continuation of his 2006 film "The Legend of Time".
At the awards ceremony of the San Sebastian Film Festival, the creators of the Argentine thriller "Red" were honored, which was noted in several nominations at once.
Benjamin Naixtat was announced director of the year, Pedro Sotero was awarded for his camerawork, and Dario Grandinetti was recognized as the best actor.
The actress of the year at the San Sebastian Film Festival was Pia Tielta from Norway.
The jury praised her participation in the film "Blind Spot" - a drama about the life of one family after the suicide attempt of the daughter.
The film became the directorial debut of the Swedish actress Tuva Novotna.
In the nomination "Best Screenplay" the victory was shared by the films "Julie" and "Faithful Man".
The special prize of the jury was received by the Philippine crime drama "Alpha: The Right to Kill".
Dizziness, tears and laughter
The Festival in San Sebastian is called one of the main cultural events in Spain and one of the most important European film competitions.
About his impressions of the festival Euronews told the owner of the "Golden Shell" director Isaki Lakuesta:
It was wonderful!
We came here as a team and of course we experienced dizzying moments, tears, laughter.
We are happy.
We started preparing this film 14 years ago, it was a very long work, and what is especially important for me is that we did not want to stop.
Now it's time for joy and gratitude.
According to Euronews correspondent Carlos Marlasca, Isaka Lacuesta's film organically fit into the collection of paintings that received the Golden Shells, "but the festival in San Sebastian was not without unexpected, sometimes shocking decisions of the jury, which are sometimes even called the hallmark of the competition."
