Given the situation that has developed, and according to the information that we have, and according to the death threats that are spreading, it is clear that we will have to go through something," the metropolitan said.
He asked for support – prayerful, moral.
Also, the viceroy of the Lavra stressed that, probably, "your physical presence will be needed."
The cleric added: "Lenin's grandchildren - in spirit, threaten reprisals, and therefore we will protect our shrine."
Those who are not indifferent to the fate of the Pochayiv Lavra - an Orthodox Ukrainian and world shrine, should be ready to protect it, the appeal says.
The Metropolitan urged not to follow the lead of those who mislead believers.
The UOC has the canonical status defined by the Tomos of October 29, 1990 from the Mother Church.
And now someone wants to make the Catholic Pope Bartholomew dependent on the Patriarch and friend.
The new style with its consequences is unacceptable to us Orthodox Christians.
And we are satisfied with the status that our church has," the viceroy of the Lavra said.
He recalled that since October 1990, the UOC has been canonically independent and completely independent in its management.
There is no administrative and financial accountability of the Moscow Patriarchate.
In fact, our church already has a Tomos.
What other Tomos do we need?" said Metropolitan Vladimir of Pochayiv, urging believers and all citizens to ask themselves whether other denominations have a Tomos, whether they are independent of the Vatican.
