Every resident of Kalmykia is a debtor
Residents of the republic are increasingly visiting the official website of the Office of the Federal Bailiff Service of Russia for the Republic of Kazakhstan.
According to specialists of the department of organizational and control work, informatization and information security of the republican department, over the past eight months, more than 140 thousand visits to the site itself have been registered, more than 42 thousand - the section "Data Bank of Enforcement Proceedings", 661 payment receipts for payment of debts have been downloaded.
According to valery Bogdanov, Chairman of the Public Council at the Federal Tax Service of Russia for the Republic of Kazakhstan, almost every resident of the region has debts for utility bills, traffic fines, bank loans, loans, and no one is insured against unforeseen situations.
But debtors can expect negative consequences in the form, for example, of a ban on traveling abroad.
That is why the Federal Tax Service of Russia for the Republic of Kazakhstan recommends that everyone who has planned a trip abroad check with the department of bailiffs at the place of residence or on the website of the www.r08fssprus.ru information about the presence of unpaid debts and repay them.
The service created a "Data Bank of Enforcement Proceedings" for the convenience of citizens.
This special electronic application is available not only on the regional websites of the FSSP of Russia, but also in social networks and mobile communications iPad, iPhone and smartphone.
The data bank contains information on enforcement proceedings initiated by Kalmyk bailiffs against all debtors, - explains Delgir Bodgaeva, assistant to the head of the FSSP of Russia for the Republic of Kazakhstan.
"If there are debts, the system displays information about the number and date of initiation of enforcement proceedings; the name of the body that issued the writ of execution or other act; its number, amount and type of debt; the address of the bailiffs' department; Full name of bailiff; contact phone.
Information on the progress of enforcement proceedings can also be obtained on the portal of public services at the address: http://epgu.gosuslugi.ru"
