Press Secretary of the President of Russia Dmitry Peskov believes that it is premature to say whether Russia will provide assistance to Serbia after the aggravation in Kosovo.
According to him, negotiations between the leaders of the two countries should take place first.
The representative of the Kremlin told reporters of the radio station "Moscow Speaks" on Sunday, September 30.
